A bishop in a chess board can move in a diagonal direction. Given two positions in the board, find the minimum number of moves to move from one point to another point.
Sample Input 1: 
Starting point : 0 0 
Ending point : 7 7

Sample Output 1: 
Minimum no of moves : 1

Sample Input 2:
Starting point : 0 0
Ending point : 0 1

Sample Output 2:
No possible moves






